column1: I look forward to our bipartisan work ahead to lift our neighbors & small businesses. There’s too much at stake & we must crush #COVID19 & get things done. Thankfully President-elect @JoeBiden has a history of bringing people together & uniting our country. Brighter days ahead!🇺🇸 https://t.co/lle11q7GGF

It's time to move forward to unite America & work together for a stronger & brighter future for all. We must all do our part to get the coronavirus under control lower health care costs & create millions of new & good-paying jobs for Americans by transitioning to clean energy. https://t.co/1XkI1I0ioO

I pledge to build bipartisan bridges continue my effort in Congress to crush the coronavirus help folks get back to work and send our children back to school safely. Right now many of our neighbors need a helping hand and our small businesses need a boost.

This is the most critical election of our lifetimes. Everything is at stake. And it all comes down to Florida. We know what’s on the ballot:  👉COVID-19 response 👉Solving the climate crisis 👉Access to quality affordable healthcare 👉A woman’s right to chose And so much more. https://t.co/Y3dg4DwJAr

⚠️ With tens of millions of Americans voting by mail in the midst of the  COVID-19 pandemic it is important that everyone make a plan to vote early NOW. If you have a mail ballot at home do not delay returning it‼️🗳  https://t.co/M6moiWVpGk
Thank you @CBCPACIE! You can count on me to stand up for affordable health care especially during the COVID19 pandemic that has hit communities of color with outsized impact. https://t.co/MCoBk0HGRP

Vote for who's working to make the economy work for middle class families not wealthy few. We need leaders who will: 👉control the spread of coronavirus  👉support small biz & help them recover from crisis 👉save $ through building clean energy economy & help us #BuildBackBetter https://t.co/ggeRhilBBq
Trump has no plan to control Covid-19 and it will continue to cost lives. He’s incoherent. #crazyuncle
Florida adds 3356 coronavirus cases 144 deaths Thursday https://t.co/v3hRZfSul1

Trump's failure to control COVID19 has put Floridians at risk and complicated their ability to return to work safely. To top it all off he is aiming to end protections for preexisting health conditions at a time when people are at risk of serious illness. https://t.co/hd1DrRbuFG

Trump has no plan to control Covid-19 no plan for health care no plan for the climate crisis no plan to boost working families.  America will vote to end the Trump chaos.  America will vote to restore dignity to 🇺🇸 and for @JoeBiden to keep us safe and #BuildBackBetter

We see the same attitude & selfish response to COVID-19. We must send Trump a clear message in November - we want a president w a plan to control the virus & who values the lives of Americans. #Gaslighter

7mos later & Trump is still no closer to executing an overarching plan to combat the coronavirus pandemic. Thousands of constituents have lost their jobs & tragically many have lost their loved ones—but Ivanka Trump came to #Tampa today to pat herself & her father on the back.

Ivanka Trump spent the afternoon in my district papering over the suffering Donald Trump has caused Floridians because he lied to the American people & then failed to act when we needed decisive leadership. Americans are less safe because of Trump’s failed coronavirus response. https://t.co/bWgkYwtohD

#HispanicHeritageMonth2020 is a time for us to honor & celebrate the great historical social & cultural contributions of our Hispanic neighbors. Together we must work to address significant disparities which the current COVID-19 pandemic has exposed. https://t.co/LgYCT5tWW1

👉 🇺🇸 @DonnaShalala is a leader and fighter for #Miami families during the COVID19 crisis & everyday. #MiamiDadeCounty: send her back to Congress to fight for affordable health care & lower drug costs! https://t.co/FA9CePkkna

🙋🏽‍♀️👨‍👩‍👧‍👦🧑🏻‍🦼🧑🏻‍🎓 #Florida families can count on @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris to stand up for higher wages affordable health care ... and a comprehensive plan to control #COVID19! https://t.co/ta7P5LydpN

Let’s work together w @JoeBiden to make America safe from #COVID19 & it’s economic fallout. That’s what a president does. Trump is unable and unwilling to be the moral leader our country needs right now.

From #COVID19 to racial injustice to the #climatecrisis - the common thread is a president who refuses to listen lead & unite our nation. We need to elect @JoeBiden & @KamalaHarris to save the soul of our nation and return faith in America. https://t.co/o1EgjBerCb

Let’s elect more Democrats to Congress so we can control COVID19 solve the climate crisis and work for universal health care. Thanks @dccc and @SpeakerPelosi for the opportunity to celebrate the #BidenHarris ticket & build a Democratic House majority that works #ForThePeople! https://t.co/stCnqigdnk

Trump's plan to defund Social Security & Medicare will harm disabled & older neighbors. #Florida is already suffering Trump's incoherent #COVID19 response. We need a leader who won't fail our community in times of crisis- that's why I stand with @JoeBiden https://t.co/af1X3diT1K

🇺🇸 families need help to get thru COVID days but Trump‘s payroll tax deferral for folks who have jobs will weaken Social Security & Medicare at a time people need help the most. Senate GOP waited months to negotiate & they need to return to the table now. https://t.co/lsK7MC69nA

👉#TampaBay ranks among least affordable areas for minimum wage workers. We need to #RaiseTheWage & treat these workers -particularly those on #COVID19 frontlines- w/ respect. They're doing tough jobs to keep us safe & healthy & they deserve a livable wage https://t.co/atYL09q8cc

I can’t get over @realDonaldTrump doesn’t know 🇺🇸’s beautiful @YosemiteNPS 😳   I’m appalled at his deranged ego that he’s done more for Afr Americans than John Lewis 😣  But mostly I’m outraged that another 245 #Floridians reported dead frm #Covid &he says “It is what it is”😤

House passed the #HeroesAct TEN weeks ago. Democrats acted to extend the $600 fed unemployment benefit for neighbors who lost their job because of the coronavirus pandemic. Republicans waited until the last minute to announce their plan to plan to cut aid to workers & families 😤 https://t.co/wWH9IEY15c

It didn’t have to be this bad. America can fight coronavirus & save lives w/ right leadership. #HEROESAct passed by the House in May (‼️) directs Trump administration to implement strategic plan incl' testing tracing isolating & help to local communities https://t.co/nHtLQtUDEo
🤔 @GovRonDeSantis says he's not following what Congress is considering for #COVID19 emergency aid I’m happy to get you up to speed Governor.   (THREAD 🧵 1/3) https://t.co/8p5gKFznQM

Local health officials have told me that they are treating more patients with #COVID19 than ever before. Please support our hospitals & frontline workers👉🏻 #stayhome if possible 🏠 & wear a mask 😷 so that we can stop this rapid community spread.  https://t.co/PjDhScsgQd

🚨 Public health experts & policymakers are alarmed at President Trump’s latest move to control #COVID19 data.  The public has a right to know - it’s “public” info after all‼️ He is trying to paint a rosy picture by sidestepping the CDC... https://t.co/ICzQ6AUjtE

If #Florida were a country we would rank in the top 5 for new #COVID19 infections worldwide based on the latest daily increases. We must do this now or else it will get worse much worse.  https://t.co/4phX4T8M6M

🗣️ #Florida! Public health experts & our hospitals are advising that we are in a critical period for #COVID19. In order to keep our families safe & hospitals functioning well 👉🏻 wear a mask wash your hands frequently & stay out of crowds. https://t.co/dGFm18op4E

🚨 Important news! 🚨 Americans from all walks of life are coming together for #TeamJoe. As we grapple with COVID-19 confront systemic racism & tackle the #ClimateCrisis we are unified in our duty to future generations 🤝🌎 https://t.co/RCsT5VnCcG
I’m going to stand up for you to lower costs improve the Affordable Care Act fight for universal coverage and protect your care during #Covid19. #ACA #ProtectOurCare  https://t.co/2FDiXjwsoG
The health safety and well-being of our neighbors are paramount and we need a serious plan during this unprecedented #COVID19 crisis.

Stay safe neighbors! Local leaders are stepping up to protect our communities and families. Meanwhile the president and @GovRonDeSantis are failing to listen to scientists 🧑🏼‍🔬 and public health experts👩🏽‍⚕️ and are failing to control the spread of #COVID19. 😳 https://t.co/mrls9e7xMP

Governor Desantis needs to be serious about holding secure & safe elections in #Florida. A bipartisan group of Supervisors of Elections have been urging and warning @GovRonDeSantis for months about the need for flexibility to run their elections in light of the coronavirus. https://t.co/0IdzuoFqGE

Stay safe friends! #Florida is experiencing spike in #COVID19 cases & unfortunately Trump admin has failed to provide widespread rapid testing plan & supplies that we need. So it’s important that we work together to keep our families & neighbors safe 🤗 https://t.co/wzGKFMbLrT

#TampaBay's small biz & nonprofits urgently need flexibility to cover costs during this public health crisis. The #HeroesAct improves the Payroll Protection Program to ensure that it reaches underserved communities & provides more help for #COVID19 emergency grants. https://t.co/8zjmrJvVUL

With 100000 lives lost to the #COVID19 pandemic in the U.S. we have reached a grim & sad milestone in less than 4 months. According to @JohnsHopkins the U.S. has the most number of infections & deaths than any other country. https://t.co/3ungMSJ17p

There’s been a troubling pattern of withholding imp’t data by Gov since #COVID19: 👉infections 👉cases at nursing homes & prisons 👉redacted public medical examiner data & was sued for doing so  Lives are at risk. The public deserves honesty & transparency https://t.co/8VRLaDO4Mb https://t.co/SvXAFhGwzR

I’ve been pressing @GovRonDeSantis/@HealthyFla to be upfront & transparent w/ Floridians about #COVID19 info. It’s vital policymakers listen to scientists who are fully informed about the scale of the pandemic. Governor this is no time for censorship or playing “hide the ball”! https://t.co/EreFlarDKW

Clean air & water protections are central to the wellbeing of our families as we fight a respiratory disease like #COVID19. You can count on me to stand up for climate justice & environmental safeguards to protect our neighbors! 🙋🏼‍♀️🌎
It will also help cushion the economic blow of the coronavirus crisis to our neighbors' pockets with another round of cash assistance to individuals 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦👨‍👨‍👧 https://t.co/5klSxNHb71

🚨More details coming out re retaliation of scientist 👉 If @GovRonDeSantis & @HealthyFla want to ensure that Floridians feel safe they must be transparent about infections tests disparities deaths etc. They’re risking lives when they hide info needed to contain #COVID19. https://t.co/gff2osth7Q
Another Trump distraction from his chaotic handling of the COVID19 public health crisis... Trump wants to waste America’s time and $ with bogus investigations 😒 https://t.co/1rlH8YODbT

I hope you saw the warm #Tampa welcome to VP @JoeBiden with a few of my friends at the first virtual rally! 👏 Floridians know that Joe is a proven & trusted leader who listens to scientists & public health experts whether its COVID19 clean air clean water or clean energy 🌎 https://t.co/hFcBAW3Kz2

🙋‍♀️I am an outspoken advocate for our public health clean air & clean water & a national leader on solutions to the #climatecrisis. The optimism & resilience of the American people are key to tackling the #COVID19 pandemic & costly #climatechange. (2/3)

The #ClimateCrisis is likely to exacerbate public health crises like #COVID19 due to air pollution - especially on vulnerable people. So I was thrilled to be joined by  👉@TeamJoe for #Florida👈 & other local climate leaders to discuss VP Biden’s #ClimateActionPlan for America🌎 https://t.co/VpPWyBJVPJ

It’s no secret that Trump has never liked the #USPS & now that it’s suffering due to #coronavirus he’s aiming to get rid of this critical government agency. USPS has been working tirelessly during this crisis to deliver supplies & mail and is a lifeline to so many of our seniors https://t.co/sGUlDY9UJo

However if you’re a member of an at-risk population exhibiting symptoms or have been exposed to a diagnosed case of #coronavirus we encourage you to return that vote by mail ballot. ✉️ #FloridaPrimary

If you’re feeling healthy and are NOT exhibiting any symptoms & have not been exposed to the #Coronavirus I encourage you to #EarlyVote this weekend or go to the polls on #ElectionDay this Tuesday. 🗳 #FloridaPrimary
